title: Browns lose in San Diego
text:
Posted Sunday, October 4th 2015 @ 8pm 
The Browns gave the the San Diego Chargers two chances to beat them on Sunday and the Chargers took advantage as Josh Lambo nailed a 34 yard field goal to beat the Browns 30-27. 
The Chargers went 57 yards on eight plays in 2:09 on the final drive. The Browns tied the game on the previous drive when Josh McCown hit Gary Barnidge for a 1 yard Touchdown and then hit Taylor Gabriel for the two point conversion that tied the game at 27. 
Lambo then missed his first attempt from 39 yards , but Tremon Williams left early and was called for offsides giving the Chargers a 2nd attempt at the win which they capitalized on. 
Arnie Hamilton
